SIMPLE: incus
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Incus
<hw>In"cus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.,
anvil.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>An anvil.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>One of the small bones in the
tympanum of the ear; the anvil bone. See <er>Ear</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The central portion of the
armature of the pharynx in the <phylum>Rotifera</phylum>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incuse</ent>⟦br⟧
